# Development tooling styling (Query Devtools)

## Decision (ALP-36)

Query Devtools stays in `@ailuracode/alpine-query-kit` but ships from the
**`@ailuracode/alpine-query-kit/devtools`** subpath. The main package entry
remains headless.

This is a **narrow, path-scoped exception** to the headless CSS policy. The
global headless rule in `new-package.mdc` is unchanged.

## Allowed only under `packages/query-kit/src/devtools/**`

- Hardcoded colors, shadows, spacing, borders, and complete panel markup
- Host theme detection via `data-theme`, `.dark`, and `prefers-color-scheme`
- Namespaced devtools tokens (`--aq-*`) and classes (`aq-devtools-*`)

## Requirements

1. Styles MUST be scoped to the devtools root element — never global document styles.
2. Tokens MUST use the `--aq-*` / `aq-devtools-*` namespace (not `data-theme` on consumer markup).
3. Devtools MUST be opt-in via `@ailuracode/alpine-query-kit/devtools` — the main entry MUST NOT statically import devtools UI.
4. Theme behavior (`light` | `dark` | `system`) MUST stay covered by `packages/query-kit/test/theme.test.ts`.

## Prohibited elsewhere in `packages/**`

Do not copy devtools styling patterns into headless plugins. `repo:check` scans
for `UI_STYLES`, `--aq-*` tokens, `aq-devtools-*` classes, and host theme
selectors outside exempt paths.

## Consumer imports

```ts
// Production — cache + Nanostores adapter only
import queryKit from "@ailuracode/alpine-query-kit";

// Development — styled panel (separate bundle)
import { queryDevtoolsPlugin } from "@ailuracode/alpine-query-kit/devtools";
```
